From 279c15a0f699d93cec875925c1308ae3d7d5fed9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:51:22 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/9] [DOSKUTSU] cmake: drop find_package(JPEG REQUIRED)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: Cave Story (the 2004 freeware EN release that doskutsu
targets) ships zero .jpg assets — confirmed by the #27 NXEngine source audit
plus a scan of the extracted asset tree (only .pbm, .bmp, .png, .pxm, .pxe,
.pxa, .org, .pxt). NXEngine-evo's `find_package(JPEG REQUIRED)` is a hard
build dependency that gates the whole build, but the resulting libjpeg
symbol is never referenced by the engine. On DJGPP cross-builds where
libjpeg isn't installed in the sysroot, this `REQUIRED` find_package fails
the configure step before any source compilation begins.

Drops:
- `find_package(JPEG REQUIRED)` from CMakeLists.txt:60.
- `${JPEG_LIBRARY}` from the `PLATFORM STREQUAL "pc"` target_link_libraries
  call (line 135 — the only path the doskutsu DJGPP cross-build exercises).

Left intact:
- `${JPEG_LIBRARY}` references in the Vita and Switch platform branches
  (lines 141 and 175) — those branches are gated by `PLATFORM STREQUAL`
  and are unreachable in the DOS build. Leaving them alone keeps the
  patch surface minimal and the diff against unrelated platforms clean.

This is patch 0001 of the Phase 4'd DJGPP port-glue series, applied before
the SDL3 migration patches (0010+).
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 1586687..58f166f 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -57,7 +57,10 @@ ENDIF()
 find_package(SDL2_mixer REQUIRED)
 find_package(SDL2_image REQUIRED)
 find_package(PNG REQUIRED)
-find_package(JPEG REQUIRED)
+# JPEG dropped: Cave Story ships no .jpg assets (verified in #27 audit) and
+# SDL2_image/SDL3_image is built without JPEG support in the doskutsu pipeline.
+# Removing the find_package call avoids a hard dependency on libjpeg in the
+# DJGPP cross-toolchain.
 
 include_directories(${SDL2_INCLUDE_DIR})
 include_directories(${SDL2_MIXER_INCLUDE_DIR})
@@ -132,7 +135,7 @@ IF(PLATFORM STREQUAL "pc")
             ENDIF()
         ENDIF()
     ENDIF()
-    target_link_libraries(nx ${SDL2_LIBRARY} ${SDL2_MIXER_LIBRARY} ${SDL2_IMAGE_LIBRARY} ${PNG_LIBRARY} ${JPEG_LIBRARY})
+    target_link_libraries(nx ${SDL2_LIBRARY} ${SDL2_MIXER_LIBRARY} ${SDL2_IMAGE_LIBRARY} ${PNG_LIBRARY})
 
 ELSEIF(PLATFORM STREQUAL "vita")
     add_definitions("-std=gnu++11")
